                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3057dc84/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>to celebrate our betrothal and we<lb/> appointed our wedding-day to be<lb/>\n                <add>אסרו חג של שבועות הב\"על</add> It is <persName>Miss Ulman's</persName> as\n                well<lb/> as my greatest wish that you would<lb/> be kind enough to come to <hi\n                    rend=\"underline\"><placeName>Wmspt</placeName></hi>. to<lb/> perform the marriage\n                ceremony for<lb/> us.</p>\n            <p>At the same time I can inform you<lb/> that we had an examination of the<lb/> Hebrew\n                and German School together<lb/> with an exhibition of the Sabbath<lb/> School on the\n                first day of <add>חה\"מ של פסח</add><lb/> which went off very nicely and to the<lb/>\n                greatest satisfaction of all the members<lb/> of the Congregation. The children\n                are<lb/> all doing right well and would be<lb/> worthy noticing those who excelled,\n                but<lb/> since you are not personally acquainted<lb/> with them it may not be so\n                interesting<lb/> to you.</p>\n            <p>Our new Congregation is also doing right<lb/> well and since there is County\n                Court</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3057dc84/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
